div1.q:
Style A (V. 1): 146–230, 236–240 A. H. Characteristics: 1st, 2nd and sometimes 3rd quarters of margin rectilinear;
from about 200 A. H. on, mostly 1st and 2nd quarters rectilinear; the borders are mostly triple-beaded, but sometimes double-beaded,
single-beaded or double-linear; the only style with "200" written مئتين.
